# claude-mem-bridge.cron — UM v0.6 §4.3 (cron template for non-systemd Linux + minimal images)
#
# Install:
#   crontab -e   # then paste the line below
# Or:
#   (crontab -l 2>/dev/null; cat installer/bridge-templates/claude-mem-bridge.cron) | crontab -
#
# Required env: source ~/.um/bridge.env first (UM_SERVER_URL, UM_AUTH_TOKEN, UM_VAULT_DIR).
# UM_BRIDGE_JITTER_SEC=600 → CLI sleeps a random 0–600s before ingesting so concurrent
# users on the same host don't stampede the reindex endpoint at :00.

# m h dom mon dow  cmd
0 */6 * * *  . $HOME/.um/bridge.env && UM_BRIDGE_JITTER_SEC=600 $HOME/.local/bin/um-bridge-claude-mem --once
